I want to write a CLI that fetches CSV files from an SFTP server,
transforms them, and loads them into a database. It's Python, and I
need a reproducible environment where every developer on my team gets
the same Python version and the same pinned dependencies.

Here is a simplified version of my transform step — it uppercases the
name column:

#+begin_src python :tangle transform.py
"""Tiny CSV transform: read from stdin, uppercase the name column, write to stdout."""
import csv
import sys

reader = csv.DictReader(sys.stdin)
writer = csv.DictWriter(sys.stdout, fieldnames=reader.fieldnames, lineterminator="\n")
writer.writeheader()
for row in reader:
    row["name"] = row["name"].upper()
    writer.writerow(row)
#+end_src

And a sample input file:

#+begin_src bash :tangle sample.csv :shebang "" :eval no-export :comments no :padline no
name,email
alice,alice@example.com
bob,bob@example.com
#+end_src

First I set up my Dagger project and install daggerlib:

#+begin_src bash :eval no-export
dagger init --sdk=python
dagger install github.com/Konubinix/daggerlib
#+end_src

The following is only for testing purposes — it makes the project
use the local daggerlib checkout instead of the published version:

#+begin_src bash :eval no-export
sed -i '/pin/d; s|"github.com/Konubinix/daggerlib@main"|"../.."|; s|"\.\./\.\.",|"../.."|' dagger.json
#+end_src

Then I write my Dagger module. Each =<<...>>= reference is defined in
the sections below:

#+begin_src python :tangle .dagger/src/python_environment/main.py :noweb yes
from typing import Annotated

import dagger
from dagger import DefaultPath, dag, function, object_type


@object_type
class PythonEnvironment:
    <<transform>>
    <<check-requests>>
    <<transform-debian>>
    <<pip-lock>>
#+end_src

* Running the transform in a clean environment

  I write a Dagger function that gets a Python container, injects my
  script and data, and runs the transform:

  #+NAME: python_transform
  #+begin_src fixtureyaml :eval no-export
userfunction: transform
project: examples/python_environment
func: alpine-python-user-venv
chain:
  - with-file:
      path: /app/transform.py
      source: "${ROOT}/examples/python_environment/transform.py"
  - with-file:
      path: /app/sample.csv
      source: "${ROOT}/examples/python_environment/sample.csv"
  - with-exec: [sh, -c, "python3 transform.py < sample.csv"]
  - stdout
  #+end_src

#+RESULTS: python_transform
:results:
#+NAME: transform
#+begin_src python
@function
async def transform(self, src: Annotated[dagger.Directory, DefaultPath(".")]) -> str:
    """Generated from test spec."""
    return await (
        dag.lib().alpine_python_user_venv()
        .with_file('/app/transform.py', src.file('transform.py'))
        .with_file('/app/sample.csv', src.file('sample.csv'))
        .with_exec(['sh', '-c', 'python3 transform.py < sample.csv'])
        .stdout()
    )
#+end_src

